        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Make the dough",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Heat the oven to 220°C fan (240°C conventional) and line a baking tray with baking paper. Combine {{wholemeal-bread-flour}}, {{plain-flour}}, {{baking-powder}}, {{sea-salt-fine}}, and {{caster-sugar}} in a large bowl. Add {{unsalted-butter}} and rub in quickly until the mixture resembles coarse crumbs with some pea-sized pieces remaining. Pour in {{whole-milk}} and mix briefly with a fork until the dough just comes together; it will be sticky and rough. Do not overwork.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Shape and bake",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Tip the dough onto a lightly floured surface and pat to 2.5 cm thickness without rolling, rolling develops the gluten and toughens the scones. Cut into 6 cm rounds with a straight-sided cutter or a sharp knife. Place on the prepared tray close together for softer sides or spaced apart for crustier ones. Brush the tops with beaten {{eggs}}. Bake for 12 to 15 minutes until well risen and deep brown on top; the base should sound hollow when tapped. Transfer to a cooling rack and eat warm.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Notes",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "All-wholemeal scones are denser but more flavourful. Reduce the milk by 10 ml as wholemeal absorbs more liquid.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Twist-cutting with a round cutter seals the sides and prevents a good rise. Press and lift straight down.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "For savoury wholemeal scones: omit the sugar and fold in 75 g of grated strong cheddar and a pinch of mustard powder.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
